title_full:
Alice Coltrane Featuring Pharoah Sanders

              —
              Journey In Satchidananda
            
              (Verve)
label: Verve
description:
Alice Coltrane and Pharoah Sanders’ definitive avant-jazz opus available on vinyl again as part of Verve’s Acoustic Sounds Series.

Widely regarded a sacred contribution to the exploratory phase of late ’60s and early ‘70s avant-garde, modal jazz, Journey In Satchidananda finds Alice Coltrane and Pharoah Sanders channelling a staggering flux of emotions - lushness, fury, melancholy and a spectrum of integers between - through a uniquely free fusion of far-flung styles and ideas. label: Rhino
description:
The nine track, 35-minute album features a previously unreleased home studio cassette recording of Prince at his piano captured in 1983.

label: ART YARD
description:
Originally released on Saturn Records in 1979, this studio recording by the large Ra ensemble (including electric guitar and electric bass) features the first recordings of the titles included on them (though most were played live a few months earlier).

label: Poole Music
description:
Fabled Western Mass percussionist Jake Meginsky channels the teachings of his late mentor Milford Graves on this shockingly dynamic set of rhythmic experiments, assembling controlled, ping-ponging lattices of electronics that sound as ornate as a gamelan orchestra and as future-shocked as latter-day Autechre. If yr into Anthony Manning's cultish 'Islets in Pink Polypropylene', this one's for you.

title_full:
Klein

              —
              Touched By An Angel
            
              (Parkwuud Entertainment)
label: Parkwuud Entertainment
description:
Preeminent avant-R&B mutator Klein spirals into free jazz gospel synth mode on a 93 minute magnum opus - proper AOTY level material - gelling tripped out synths and a haul of personal recordings in a breathtaking elevation of an already unique sound - masterful work for fans of Actress, Laurel Halo, Elysia Crampton/E+E, Mica Levi, Leyland Kirby, Dubplate Drama and the early era of Pixar x disney collabs.
